Package edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.search

Class Result<A extends Action>

java.lang.Object
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.search.Result<A>
Type Parameters:
A - the type of action used in this result's solution
public class Result<A extends Action> extends Object
A result object summarizes information about the outcome of a search (like the solution it found) and the effort spent reaching that outcome (like the number of nodes visited and the time spent searching).
Author:
Stephen G. Ware

    • Result

      public Result(Search<A> search, Worker.Status status)
      Performs a search and constructs a result based on the outcome. This constructor is used by Search.get(Status) to ensure that this result object is allocated in memory before the search starts, in case an OutOfMemoryError occurs during search.
      Parameters:
      search - the search whose next solution will be generated
      status - a status to update while the search runs

    • getSuccess

      public boolean getSuccess()
      Indicates whether or not this result represents success in solving the problem; success means a solution was found that the utility it achieved is greater than or equal to the search's goal.
      Returns:
      true if this result includes a solution which achieves a utility that is greater than or equal to the goal, false otherwise
